  "texts": [
    "Let us consider a list of length l composed of sensitive entities, se, that are in an original clinical note, ON, of length L. For a certain sensitive entity of this list, se i, we start by computing its length, e. We then slide a window of length e across the anonymized note, AN, with a step of one character, and compute the LRa between each window and se i.",
    "The Levenshtein Similarity Index (LSI) of se i against AN is given by the following expression, where w j represents the jth window of length e within AN.",
    "L-e max j=1 LRa(se i, w j)",
    "This measure represents the maximum similarity between se i and the content of AN.",
    "Having a list, S, of the LSIs measured for each entity contained in se, the Average Levenshtein Index of Dissimilarity (ALID) is given as follows, where ⟨S⟩ is the mean value of S:"
  ],
